        "content": [
          "Spanish verbs come in 3 families:",
          "-AR (hablar)  -ER (comer)  -IR (vivir)",
          "",
          "Each family shares the same endings.",
          "Here's -AR, the most common:         Press 1",
          "",
          "yo hablo             = I speak",
          "tú hablas            = you speak",
          "él/ella habla        = he/she speaks",
          "nosotros hablamos    = we speak",
          "ellos hablan         = they speak",
          "",
          "The pattern: drop -ar, add",
          "-o, -as, -a, -amos, -an",
          "",
          "You can often drop the pronoun because",
          "the ending tells you who's speaking.",
          "Hablo = I speak. Hablan = they speak."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lección tres",
        "pronunciation_mappings": {
          "1": "yo hablo, tú hablas, él habla, nosotros hablamos, ellos hablan"
        }
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "-ER verbs (comer = to eat):         Press 1",
          "",
          "yo como             = I eat",
          "tú comes            = you eat",
          "él/ella come        = he/she eats",
          "nosotros comemos    = we eat",
          "ellos comen         = they eat",
          "",
          "-IR verbs (vivir = to live):        Press 2",
          "",
          "yo vivo             = I live",
          "tú vives            = you live",
          "él/ella vive        = he/she lives",
          "nosotros vivimos    = we live",
          "ellos viven         = they live",
          "",
          "Notice: -ER and -IR are almost",
          "identical! Only nosotros differs."
        ],
        "pronunciation_mappings": {
          "1": "yo como, tú comes, él come, nosotros comemos, ellos comen",
          "2": "yo vivo, tú vives, él vive, nosotros vivimos, ellos viven"
        }
      }
